anguage of the code block,\\\nthus if you want to run the python code replace `r` with `python`\n\nIf you want to only display the result but not the code, it is also possible\\\n```{r, echo = FALSE}\n```","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### Discussion Questions\n1. Describe the following data types: numeric, character, logical, factor.\\\n- Answer: numeric:numerical data, either integer, integers values can be also represented with an `L` right next to the integer\\\ncharacter: character strings quoted with single or double quotes\\\nlogcial: TRUE or FALSE\\\nfactor:categorical data \\\n2. Why is a vector known as a homogeneous data structure?\\\n- because vector is contained of homogenous data types\n3. Give an example of a heterogeneous data structure in R.\\\n- strings and factor\n4. What is the difference between NA and \"NA\"?\\\n- NA represents missing data while \"NA\" is a string \n5. What operator is used to return named elements of a list and named columns of a dataframe?\\\n- []\n6. Describe some functions that are used to manipulate dataframes.\\\n- `cbind()`, `rbind()', \n7. What is a package and how do you install and use a new package?\\\n- package is a set of programmes grouped together, to use a package we need to install it using install.packages() function and then use library() function to load it, to use any specific function in a package, we need to specify the package name and add the function name using :: such as `packagename::functionname()`\n8. Describe what is meant by ‘namespacing’ and why it might be useful.\\\n- namespacing is the organisation of functions with the same name, it avoids confusion of different functions with the same name\n9. What is the pipe operator, and why is it popular in R?\\\n- pipe operator in R puts the result of an operation and use it as an input in an operation next to it, it is popular because it makes the code blocks more readable \n10. What is the difference between an error and a warning in R?\\\n- error indicates the mistakes in the code while warning is just to inform\n11. Name some simple plotting functions in base R.\n- plotly\n- boxplot\n12. Name some common specialist plotting and graphing packages in R.\n- ggplot\n- GGally\n13. What is R Markdown, and why is it useful to someone performing analysis using programming languages?\n- R markdown is the documentation of a coding process making it reproducable by the reader and provides explanation of certain utisalitions ","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Statistics Foundation \nParticularly important 3 topics in this book \n1. Descriptive statistics of populations and samples \n2. Distribution of random variables \n3. Hypothesis testing \n\nThe dataset used in this chapter is still the `salespeople` dataset loaded earlier in this notebook ","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# assign the link to the variable 'url'\nurl <- \"http://peopleanalytics-regression-book.org/data/salespeople.csv\"\n\n# read the url using read.csv() function and assign it to the variable salespeople\nsalespeople <- read.csv(url)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-05-16T14:32:05.550172Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-05-16T14:32:05.551990Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-05-16T14:32:05.955386Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":49,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# let's see the structure of the data set using str() function \nstr(salespeople)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-05-16T14:32:10.207263Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-05-16T14:32:10.209035Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-05-16T14:32:10.232697Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":50,"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"'data.frame':\t351 obs. of  4 variables:\n $ promoted     : int  0 0 1 0 1 1 0 0 0 0 ...\n $ sales        : int  594 446 674 525 657 918 318 364 342 387 ...\n $ customer_rate: num  3.94 4.06 3.83 3.62 4.4 4.54 3.09 4.89 3.74 3 ...\n $ performance  : int  2 3 4 2 3 2 3 1 3 3 ...\n","output_type":"stream"}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# It looks like `promoted` is binary, containing only 0 and 1 value\n# display the unique values in promoted using unique() function \nunique(salespeople$promoted)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-05-16T14:32:11.416115Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-05-16T14:32:11.417956Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-05-16T14:32:11.439380Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":51,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/html":"<style>\n.list-inline {list-style: none; margin:0; padding: 0}\n.list-inline>li {display: inline-block}\n.list-inline>li:not(:last-child)::after {content: \"\\00b7\"; padding: 0 .5ex}\n</style>\n<ol class=list-inline><li>0</li><li>1</li></ol>\n","text/markdown":"1. 0\n2. 1\n\n\n","text/latex":"\\begin{enumerate*}\n\\item 0\n\\item 1\n\\end{enumerate*}\n","text/plain":"[1] 0 1"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Which proves our hypothesis that promoted contains only two values 0 and 1\n\nPerformance values seem like categorical, let's display the unique values","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"unique(salespeople$performance)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-05-16T14:32:15.270901Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-05-16T14:32:15.272766Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-05-16T14:32:15.293305Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":52,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/html":"<style>\n.list-inline {list-style: none; margin:0; padding: 0}\n.list-inline>li {display: inline-block}\n.list-inline>li:not(:last-child)::after {content: \"\\00b7\"; padding: 0 .5ex}\n</style>\n<ol class=list-inline><li>2</li><li>3</li><li>4</li><li>1</li><li>&lt;NA&gt;</li></ol>\n","text/markdown":"1. 2\n2. 3\n3. 4\n4. 1\n5. &lt;NA&gt;\n\n\n","text/latex":"\\begin{enumerate*}\n\\item 2\n\\item 3\n\\item 4\n\\item 1\n\\item <NA>\n\\end{enumerate*}\n","text/plain":"[1]  2  3  4  1 NA"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"We can confirm that it is categorical ","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 3.1 Elementary descriptive statistics of populations and samples \n### 3.1.1 Mean, variance and standard deviation \n\nWhile the mean value of a sample is represented by x, and mean value of the entire dataset is denoted using &mu;","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# display the mean value of different columns in salespeople dataset \n# display mean value of the column sales \nmean(salespeople$sales, na.rm = TRUE) # na.rm indicates that the NA values are to be ignored ","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-05-16T14:32:19.037468Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-05-16T14:32:19.039421Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-05-16T14:32:19.060968Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":53,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/html":"527.005714285714","text/markdown":"527.005714285714","text/latex":"527.005714285714","text/plain":"[1] 527.0057"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# \nmean(salespeople$promoted, na.rm = TRUE)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-05-16T14:34:44.159299Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-05-16T14:34:44.161095Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-05-16T14:34:44.179204Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":55,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/html":"0.321937321937322","text/markdown":"0.321937321937322","text/latex":"0.321937321937322","text/plain":"[1] 0.3219373"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Since the output of promoted column can be only 1 or 0, meaning being promoted or not, we can interpret this result of 0.3 as the percentage of one being promoted, if it is random, then the result should have been 0.5, since it's lower than 0.5, we would infer that most people are not promoted ","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"mean(salespeople$performance, na.rm = TRUE)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-05-16T14:35:28.593902Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-05-16T14:35:28.595670Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-05-16T14:35:28.613105Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":58,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/html":"2.5","text/markdown":"2.5","text/latex":"2.5","text/plain":"[1] 2.5"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Since the performance rating can only range from 1 to 4, we can infer that the overall rating of performance is above 0.5 * 4 = 2 level ","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-05-16T14:36:36.247899Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-05-16T14:36:36.279689Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-05-16T14:36:36.333720Z"}}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"The variance is a measure of how much data varies around its mean.\\\nThere are two types of definitions of variance : \n1. The population variance : average squared difference from the mean \n2. Sample variance : Bessel's correction is applied\\\nIn R, by default, sample variance is calculated ","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"sample_variance_sales <- var(salespeople$sales, na.rm = TRUE)\nsample_variance_sales","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-05-16T14:47:45.228368Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-05-16T14:47:45.230912Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-05-16T14:47:45.274687Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":62,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/html":"34308.1145804339","text/markdown":"34308.1145804339","text/latex":"34308.1145804339","text/plain":"[1] 34308.11"},"metadata":{}}]}]}